Doc Spatz,<br>
     My understanding about &quot;Xin Loi&quot;, whatever its correct literal meaning, is basically &quot;Sorry 'Bout That&quot; with an overlay of &quot;Tough Bananas&quot; or something stronger.  And I was referring mostly to my difference of view with my oldest son.  The &quot;Philly Speak&quot; with &quot;ADDYTUDE!&quot; is in that context.  I just couldn't resist a side note on your previous brush with &quot;Xin Loi&quot;.                                                                                               Besides the sandwich, there's the Philly soft pretzels, Birch Beer and the original cheese fries plus a hundred other fast food goodies to clog your arteries right proper if you ever visit.                                                                                                      One more thing - you might see the Franco-Vietnamese &quot;beaucoup Dien Cai Dau&quot; (the latter shortened often to Dinky Dau); which refers to varying degrees of &quot;very crazy&quot; a la say John Belushi.
